50|$|In low-frequency {{applications}} involving loaded or nonloaded <b>vertical</b> <b>antennas,</b> {{the effective}} height {{is the moment}} of the current distribution in the vertical section, divided by the input current. For an antenna with a symmetrical current distribution, the center of radiation is the center of the distribution. For an antenna with asymmetrical current distribution, the center of radiation is the center of current moments when viewed from points near the direction of maximum radiation.|$|R
